<br>
Persephone spots Hera with Hypnos and walks over to her with a beaming shining smile. Curtsies and gives her a sincere hug and kiss on the cheek, both full of love:: Hello Aunty Hera, how are you today? I have not seen you since I left for the Underworld.<br>
<br>
::Persephone knew, along with everyone else, how her majesty felt being at the same occasion with Zeus. For everyone knew where and what he was doing before he came to the wedding. She knew Hera by his embarassing ways and one minute affairs:: Here Hera ::hands her a small bouquet of rich, colorful yellow and red roses:: I figured you could use them. I planted, grew, and cut them from my private garden myself and they never wilt!<br>
<br>
I'm so glad Hades let me come up here, but then again, he rarely resists my requests ::looks at her with her light electric blue eyes glossy with the same tears she gives Hades. She laughs and makes them go away.:: Hades sends his love. He didn't literally say that, but I know he means it to those like you and Hypnos and Athena at. He just never says that sort of thing, because it might make him look &quot;soft&quot; ::makes the quotation marks with her fingers and rolls her eyes and laughs:: <br>
<br>
He tells me he loves me when we're alone though ::giggles pleasantly and puts a finger to her sweet shapely dark pink lips:: shh, don't tell him I said that ::smiles  and turns to Hypnos and hugs him and kisses him on the cheek:: And how are you my dear friend? I have have missed you too ::hands him some midnight blue roses and smiles ssweetly:: These won't wilt either. I think they will look beautful and pefect in your home. I think they will suit you too. Do you like them?<br>
